@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@
+## Testing user conditions across UCI + OSM + Google
+
+Use this helper to run ingestion with `uci,osm,google` and print scenario counts that map to common user preferences (cafe/library vibe, on-campus, wifi, parking, charging, open-now).
+
+Google Places requests are automatically clamped to the API-supported range for `maxResultCount` (1..20), so larger CLI `--maxResults` values will not cause Google request failures.
+
+```bash
+python scripts/testUserConditions.py --sqlitePath data/tmp_user_conditions.db --verbose
+```
+
+### Useful command variants
+
+```bash
+# Smaller radius if you only want campus-adjacent results
+python scripts/testUserConditions.py --radiusMiles 2 --maxResults 25
+
+# Full radius and larger sample (when API keys are configured)
+python scripts/testUserConditions.py --radiusMiles 5 --maxResults 75
+```
+
+### Direct pipeline runs by provider set
+
+```bash
+# Force exactly UCI + OSM + Google providers
+python scripts/runIngestion.py --providers uci,osm,google --sqlitePath data/tmp_uog.db --verbose
+
+# Compare to only campus/static and OSM
+python scripts/runIngestion.py --providers uci,osm --sqlitePath data/tmp_uo.db --verbose
+```
